  "chunk_index": 15,
  "summary": "The next morning in the city of the Crow, Xiang Yue wakes to find his room empty and Wakatsuki already departed for Kyoto. Left alone in a spacious, soundproof room with a cold breakfast, Xiang Yue listens to Schubert on the radio and reflects on the psychological effects of sensory deprivation.\n\nHis solitude is interrupted by persistent knocking at the door, which reveals two identical, beautiful girls named Miyuki and Kanae. Although Mutsu had previously described them as being approximately twenty years old, they appear to be fifteen or sixteen. They are dressed in matching pink outfits with frilly aprons and flowered hats, possessing a youthful, innocent aura and gray eyes that remain devoid of emotion regarding the deaths of their father and grandfather.\n\nThe twins interact with Xiang Yue in a synchronized, \"stereo\" fashion that he finds physically difficult to endure. After a brief misunderstanding regarding his name, the girls ask if he has found the killer of their father and grandfather. Xiang Yue admits he has not, noting their unsettling lack of grief. When the topic of the killer's identity arises, one girl suggests their great-grandfather is responsible, which triggers a heated argument between the sisters. The encounter concludes with the two girls engaging in a physical shoving match in front of a stunned Xiang Yue.",
